The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Hindi tribute to Tagore

 New Delhi, May 9: Doordarshan will soon start airing Rabindrasangeet in Hindi, reports our special correspondent

 Prime Minister Manmohan Singh will tomorrow release the first DVD of the translated Rabindranath Tagore songs at the Parliament auditorium. 

 Information and broadcasting minister Priya Ranjan Das Munshi said the event will mark the 146th birth anniversary of the poet.

 Ten such DVDs are ready and more are in the pipeline. 

 DD is planning to run the half-hour programme every Sunday night for a year. 




